**Happy 6 YEAR ANNIVERSARY Comic Book Clique!**

In this episode, we cover the 1994 cult classic **The Crow**, starring the late Brandon Lee and based on the 1989 comic. Only one of the hosts have seen this film, but did they like it? Does The Crow stand the test of time? Can you physically WILL morphine out of someone's veins? These questions plus, a discussion about Sting, gritty comic book films, and whether the hosts think a reboot would work, in this special anniversary addition of the Major Issues Podcast!  
  
Please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

  
